-- Chinese Second-Half Fiscal Revenue Growth att Least 10%, Observer Reports
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-06-28T00:49:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-28/chinese-second-half-fiscal-revenue-growth-att-least-10-observer-reports.html

          
          
             China can maintain a growth in
fiscal revenue of 10 percent in the second half of the year,
slowing from 30.8 percent in the first five months, the Economic
Observer said Monday, citing an unidentified official from State
Administration of Taxation.  
 Fiscal revenue growth for the first half of the month,
declined sharply, the report cited the official as saying.  
